    <thetext>The description of RangeError currently says: &quot;Indicates a numeric value has exceeded the allowable range.&quot; Discussions at and after the TC39 meeting in November 2011 came to the conclusion that we should allow the use of RangeError to also indicate invalid values in non-numeric types. Use cases discussed were language tags, as defined in RFC 5646, or selectors such as &quot;sort&quot; and &quot;search&quot;, both used in the ECMAScript Globalization API.</thetext>
